---
title: `$view::path()`
description: Generate full path of a view file from its ID.
...

~~~ .php.xmp
View::path($input, $fail = false);
~~~

Search for PHP file relative to the root folder based on the given name, otherwise, return `$fail`:

~~~ .php
$test_1 = View::path('page');
$test_2 = View::path('test');
~~~

Result:

~~~ .php
$test_1 = '.\page.php';
$test_2 = false;
~~~

Search for PHP files relative to the root folder based on the given _namespace_. Otherwise, return the first available alternate file, otherwise, return `$fail`:

~~~ .php
$test = View::path('page/about/social');
~~~

Result:

~~~ .php
// can be
$test = '.\page.about.social.php';
// or
$test = '.\page\about\social.php';
// or
$test = '.\page\about.php';
// or
$test = '.\page.php';
~~~